@drnic, @bodymindarts, I don't know all capabilities of ``confd `` in Nov 2015, but with the latest version it's definitely possible to extract ``host:port`` from *conn_url*:
```
        {{$data := json $member}}
        {{$conn_addr := base (replace (index (split $data.conn_url "/") 2) "@" "/" -1)}}
```

And one more thing: there is no need to search for member with ``$data.role == "master"`` and I would even say that it is totally wrong.
Instead of doing this, let the `haproxy`` to do it's job, just put all members into haproxy config and configure health-check there. You can take [haproxy.cfg](https://github.com/zalando/patroni/blob/master/haproxy.cfg) as an example. It (haproxy) determines where is the master by performing ``OPTIONS /`` request on Patroni REST API. Patroni responds with status code 200 if it is running as the master. Otherwise it will respond with 502.

If you want to do read load-balancing, it's possible to use another endpoint, ``GET /replica`` or ``OPTIONS /replica``. In this case you will get 200 only when the node running as replica.

