I ended up creating a custom `BigInt` scalar.

```
from graphene.types import Scalar
from graphql.language import ast
from graphene.types.scalars import MIN_INT, MAX_INT

class BigInt(Scalar):
    """
    BigInt is an extension of the regular Int field
        that supports Integers bigger than a signed
        32-bit integer.
    """
    @staticmethod
    def big_to_float(value):
        num = int(value)
        if num > MAX_INT or num < MIN_INT:
            return float(int(num))
        return num

    serialize = big_to_float
    parse_value = big_to_float

    @staticmethod
    def parse_literal(node):
        if isinstance(node, ast.IntValue):
            num = int(node.value)
            if num > MAX_INT or num < MIN_INT:
                return float(int(num))
            return num
```

Then I just set the necessary fields to this scalar in my schema files.  I would create a pull request, but I'm not sure how to add this into graphene-django itself.  Maybe someone more knowledgeable than myself can give it a go.

