> Or am I missing something?

Ok, I see what you mean. The model method `getRhs` will not work for Xor constraints. SCIP has different types of constraints and each of them provides its own method to query them. We have only interfaced the behavior for linear and quadratic constraints.  
One would need to extend `getRhs` with something like
```python
        elif constype == 'quadratic':
            return SCIPgetRhsQuadratic(self._scip, cons.cons)
        elif constype == 'xor':
            return SCIPgetRhsXor(self._scip, cons.cons)
```

and this would return the boolean, even though in the documentation it is written at the left side.  
On the other hand, the method `getLhs` will never work for Xor constraints, because there is no lhs. There is no `SCIPgetLhsXor`. One could return the variables, but this would differ from SCIP.  
In any case, I am unsure whether it is a good idea to extend `getRhs` so that it also returns the boolean for Xor constraints.  

